<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Check-out Comparison — {{ result.checkin.address or "Property" }}</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --ink: #1a1a1a; --muted: #5a5f6a; --rule: #d8dbe0; --accent: #15406b;
    --band: #f3f5f8; --paper: #ffffff;
    --confirm: #0e6b46; --reject: #a3231f; --pend: #8a6d1f;
    --ui: "Segoe UI Variable Text", "Segoe UI", "Avenir Next", "Helvetica Neue", sans-serif;
    --mono: "Cascadia Code", "JetBrains Mono", Consolas, monospace;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif; color: var(--ink);
         margin: 0; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.45; background: var(--paper); }
  main { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 24px; }
  h1, h2, h3 { font-weight: 600; color: var(--accent); }
  h1 { font-size: 20pt; margin-bottom: 2px; }
  h2 { font-size: 14pt; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
       padding-bottom: 4px; margin-top: 30px; }
  .kicker { letter-spacing: .22em; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 9pt;
            color: var(--muted); }
  .meta { color: var(--muted); font-size: 9pt; }
  .note { background: var(--band); padding: 10px 14px; border-left: 3px solid
          var(--accent); margin: 14px 0 18px; font-size: 10pt; }
  table.delta { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 9.5pt; }
  table.delta th { text-align: left; background: var(--accent); color: #fff;
                   padding: 6px 8px; font-weight: 600; }
  table.delta td { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); padding: 6px 8px;
                   vertical-align: top; }
  table.delta tr { page-break-inside: avoid; }
  .grade { white-space: nowrap; font-variant: small-caps; }
  .worse { color: var(--reject); font-weight: 700; }
  .better { color: var(--confirm); }
  .cls { font: 600 8.5pt var(--ui); text-transform: uppercase;
         letter-spacing: .04em; white-space: nowrap; }
  .cls.damage, .cls.cleaning { color: var(--reject); }
  .cls.fair_wear_and_tear { color: var(--confirm); }
  .cls.landlord_responsibility { color: var(--pend); }
  .cls.unclassified { color: var(--muted); }
  .pair { display: flex; gap: 14px; margin: 10px 0 22px; page-break-inside: avoid; }
  .pair .side { flex: 1; border: 1px solid var(--rule); padding: 10px; }
  .side h4 { margin: 0 0 6px; font: 600 9pt var(--ui); text-transform: uppercase;
             letter-spacing: .08em; color: var(--muted); }
  .side .photos { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; }
  .side figure { margin: 0; width: 47%; }
  .side .frame { position: relative; }
  .side img { width: 100%; display: block; border: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .side figcaption { font-size: 8pt; color: var(--muted); font-family: var(--mono); }
  .missing { font-size: 8.5pt; color: var(--muted); border: 1px dashed var(--rule);
             padding: 12px 8px; text-align: center; }
  /* Defect-region overlays: same markup + styling as report.html.j2 (the
     docs/05 Level 2 annotation boxes, reused as compare evidence anchors). */
  .region { position: absolute; border: 2px solid var(--reject);
            background: rgba(163,35,31,.08); pointer-events: none; }
  .region::after {
    content: attr(data-label); position: absolute; left: -2px; bottom: 100%;
    background: var(--reject); color: #fff; font-family: var(--ui);
    font-size: 7.5pt; padding: 1px 5px; white-space: nowrap; max-width: 220px;
    overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;
  }
  ul.defects { margin: 4px 0 4px 16px; padding: 0; color: var(--reject);
               font-size: 9pt; }
  .rationale { font-size: 9pt; margin: 6px 0 0; }
  .rationale .who { font: 600 8pt var(--ui); color: var(--muted);
                    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .06em; }
  @page {
    size: A4; margin: 16mm 14mm 20mm 14mm;
    @bottom-center { content: "Page " counter(page) " of " counter(pages);
                     font: 8pt sans-serif; color: #5a5f6a; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<main>
  <div class="kicker">Check-in vs check-out comparison</div>
  <h1>{{ result.checkin.address or "Property" }}</h1>
  <p class="meta">
    Check-in: {{ result.checkin.inspected_at }} ({{ result.checkin.backend or "?" }})
    &middot; Check-out: {{ result.checkout.inspected_at }} ({{ result.checkout.backend or "?" }})<br>
    Tenancy length: {{ result.params.tenancy_months ~ " months" if result.params.tenancy_months else "not provided" }}
    &middot; Occupancy: {{ result.params.occupancy or "not provided" }}
    &middot; Classification: {{ result.params.backend }}{{ " (" ~ result.params.model ~ ")" if result.params.model else "" }}
  </p>
  <p class="note">This is a <strong>discussion sheet</strong>: it identifies,
  evidences and classifies changes between the two reports. It does not price
  anything — deduction amounts are for the parties (and, failing agreement,
  the deposit scheme) to settle. Classifications marked
  “fair wear and tear” are not chargeable to the tenant; “unclassified”
  means no rubric ran (offline) or the rubric failed — review by hand.</p>

  <h2>1. Grade-delta summary</h2>
  <p class="meta">{{ result.totals.matched }} items matched
    ({{ result.totals.changed }} changed, {{ result.totals.unchanged }} unchanged)
    &middot; {{ result.totals.removed }} not located at check-out
    &middot; {{ result.totals.added }} new at check-out</p>
  <table class="delta">
    <thead><tr>
      <th>Item</th><th>Room</th><th>Check-in</th><th>Check-out</th>
      <th>Δ</th><th>Classification</th><th>Evidence</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for room in rooms %}{% for c in room.changed %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ c.name }}{% if c.checkin_name != c.name %}
            <div class="meta">check-in: “{{ c.checkin_name }}”</div>{% endif %}
          {% if c.new_defects %}<ul class="defects">
            {% for d in c.new_defects %}<li>{{ d }}</li>{% endfor %}
          </ul>{% endif %}
        </td>
        <td>{{ room.name }}</td>
        <td class="grade">{{ c.checkin_condition or "—" }}</td>
        <td class="grade">{{ c.checkout_condition or "—" }}</td>
        <td class="{{ 'worse' if c.grade_delta and c.grade_delta > 0 else 'better' if c.grade_delta and c.grade_delta < 0 else '' }}">
          {%- if c.grade_delta is none %}—
          {%- elif c.grade_delta > 0 %}▼{{ c.grade_delta }}
          {%- elif c.grade_delta < 0 %}▲{{ -c.grade_delta }}
          {%- else %}0{% endif %}</td>
        <td><span class="cls {{ c.classification or 'unclassified' }}">
            {{ class_labels.get(c.classification or "unclassified") }}</span></td>
        <td class="meta">in: {{ c.checkin_photo_ids | join(", ") or "—" }}<br>
            out: {{ c.checkout_photo_ids | join(", ") or "—" }}</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}{% endfor %}
    {% if not result.totals.changed %}
      <tr><td colspan="7" class="meta">No graded deterioration or new defects
        found on matched items.</td></tr>
    {% endif %}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>2. Paired photo evidence</h2>
  {% for room in rooms %}{% for c in room.changed %}
  <h3>{{ room.name }} — {{ c.name }}
    <span class="cls {{ c.classification or 'unclassified' }}">
      {{ class_labels.get(c.classification or "unclassified") }}</span></h3>
  <div class="pair">
    {% for side, photos, cond, defects in [
        ("Check-in", c.checkin_photos, c.checkin_condition, c.checkin_defects),
        ("Check-out", c.checkout_photos, c.checkout_condition, c.checkout_defects)] %}
    <div class="side">
      <h4>{{ side }} — <span class="grade">{{ cond or "not graded" }}</span></h4>
      {% if defects %}<ul class="defects">
        {% for d in defects %}<li>{{ d }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul>{% endif %}
      <div class="photos">
        {% for p in photos %}
        {% if p.src %}
        <figure>
          <div class="frame">
            <img src="{{ p.src }}" alt="{{ p.id }}">
            {% for reg in p.regions %}
            <span class="region" data-label="{{ reg.defect }}"
                  style="left:{{ '%.2f' | format(reg.x * 100) }}%;top:{{ '%.2f' | format(reg.y * 100) }}%;width:{{ '%.2f' | format(reg.w * 100) }}%;height:{{ '%.2f' | format(reg.h * 100) }}%;"></span>
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
          <figcaption>{{ p.id }}{% if p.captured_at %} &middot; {{ p.captured_at }}{% endif %}</figcaption>
        </figure>
        {% else %}
        <div class="missing">{{ p.id }}: photo file not available</div>
        {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
        {% if not photos %}<div class="missing">no photo evidence cited</div>{% endif %}
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  {% if c.rationale %}
  <p class="rationale"><span class="who">Rubric rationale</span> — {{ c.rationale }}</p>
  {% endif %}
  {% if c.resolved_defects %}
  <p class="meta">Check-in defects not re-observed at check-out:
    {{ c.resolved_defects | join("; ") }}</p>
  {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}{% endfor %}
  {% if not result.totals.changed %}<p class="meta">Nothing to show.</p>{% endif %}

  <h2>3. Items not located at check-out</h2>
  {% if result.totals.removed %}
  <table class="delta">
    <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Room</th><th>Check-in condition</th>
      <th>Check-in defects</th><th>Check-in evidence</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for room in rooms %}{% for it in room.removed %}
      <tr><td>{{ it.name }}</td><td>{{ room.name }}</td>
          <td class="grade">{{ it.condition or "—" }}</td>
          <td>{{ it.defects | join("; ") or "—" }}</td>
          <td class="meta">{{ it.photo_ids | join(", ") }}</td></tr>
    {% endfor %}{% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p class="meta">“Not located” is an alignment verdict, not a liability
  verdict: confirm each with the tenant before treating it as a loss.</p>
  {% else %}<p class="meta">None — every check-in item was matched.</p>{% endif %}

  <h2>4. Items new at check-out</h2>
  {% if result.totals.added %}
  <table class="delta">
    <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Room</th><th>Check-out condition</th>
      <th>Check-out defects</th><th>Check-out evidence</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for room in rooms %}{% for it in room.added %}
      <tr><td>{{ it.name }}</td><td>{{ room.name }}</td>
          <td class="grade">{{ it.condition or "—" }}</td>
          <td>{{ it.defects | join("; ") or "—" }}</td>
          <td class="meta">{{ it.photo_ids | join(", ") }}</td></tr>
    {% endfor %}{% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}<p class="meta">None.</p>{% endif %}

  <footer class="meta" style="margin-top:36px; text-align:center;">
    homeinventory compare &middot; alignment is lexical (room + head-noun
    match, no API calls) &middot; classifications are AI-suggested and
    require human review before any deduction discussion.
  </footer>
</main>
</body>
</html>
